# Release and CI verification

When you **ship web changes**, **push to `main`**, **create a tag**, or tell the user deployment/download is ready:

1. **Push web changes to `main`**: Run **`pnpm push`** (auto-commit + `git push origin main`). If `apps/print-agent/` changed vs last `print-agent-v*` tag and `VERSION` was bumped, push also auto-tags `print-agent-v{VERSION}` (unless `PUSH_SKIP_PRINT_AGENT_TAG=1`). Confirm **Vercel Production** is Ready after push — do not claim deployed until Vercel shows success.
2. **Tag `print-agent-v*`**: Run `scripts/check-print-agent.sh` first (or `scripts/tag-print-agent.sh`). Ensure `apps/print-agent/VERSION` matches tag. Push tag; wait for **Print agent release** (`test-linux` + Windows + **verify-release**). Release must list `MesaPrintAgent-Setup-amd64.exe` — not tag-only Source zip. Optionally `scripts/wait-for-github-release.sh <tag>`.
3. **Print-agent code changes**: Do not edit `print-agent-release.yml` unless changing the installer pipeline. Business logic stays in `apps/print-agent/*.go`; rely on print-agent-ci + test-linux for tests.
4. **Never** say print agent is downloadable based only on merge to `main` without the tag.
5. If Vercel or release fails, report the failure URL before retrying.

See `docs/ci-and-release.zh.md`.
